    • Method Detail

      • prepareForFileMove

        void prepareForFileMove(String objectKey,
                        CompleteUploadSingleParamsDto completeUploadSingleParamsDto)
        Prepares to move an S3 file from the source bucket to the target bucket. On success, both the target and source business object data statuses are set to "RE-ENCRYPTING" and the DTO is updated accordingly.
        Parameters:
        objectKey - the object key (i.e. filename)
        completeUploadSingleParamsDto - the DTO to be initialized with parameters required for complete upload single message processing

      • performFileMove

        void performFileMove(CompleteUploadSingleParamsDto completeUploadSingleParamsDto)
        Moves an S3 file from the source bucket to the target bucket. Updates the target business object data status in the DTO based on the result of S3 copy operation. If S3 copy fails, the target business object data status in the DTO is set to "INVALID", otherwise it is set to "VALID".
        Parameters:
        completeUploadSingleParamsDto - the DTO that contains complete upload single message parameters

      • executeFileMoveAfterSteps

        void executeFileMoveAfterSteps(CompleteUploadSingleParamsDto completeUploadSingleParamsDto)
        Executes the steps required to complete the processing of complete upload single message following a successful S3 file move operation. The method also updates the DTO that contains complete upload single message parameters.
        Parameters:
        completeUploadSingleParamsDto - the DTO that contains complete upload single message parameters

      • deleteSourceFileFromS3

        void deleteSourceFileFromS3(CompleteUploadSingleParamsDto completeUploadSingleParamsDto)
        delete the source file from S3
        Parameters:
        completeUploadSingleParamsDto - the DTO that contains complete upload single message parameters

      • updateBusinessObjectDataStatus
